This paper is about few-shot learning in computer vision, which is a subfield of computer science that deals with image and video analysis. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of neural networks and distance metrics, which are topics that fall under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of natural language processing techniques (cs.CL) for data augmentation. Finally, the paper discusses the use of adaptive feature extractors, which is a topic that falls under neural networks (cs.NE).
